With 148 matches since the FIFA World Cup qualification (CAF) kicked off on September 4, 2019, 10 teams have made it to the third round, the final stage of the competition. Tied in a home-away match, the first leg of the playoff holds today, while the second leg will be held four days later, on March 29, 2022. Showmax is streaming the game live and on HD, courtesy of SuperSport. The Black Stars of Ghana will take on the Super Eagles of Nigeria at Baba Yara Stadium at 8:30 pm today, while the Eagles welcome their West Africa opponent in the second leg at M.K.O Abiola Stadium, Abuja, at 6.00 pm prompt on Tuesday. The Eagles of Mali are hoping to secure their first ticket into the World Cup, as they welcome The Carthage Eagles of Tunisia today at Stade du 26 Mars (Martyrs of Pentecost Stadium), Mali. The second leg will hold at Stade Olympique Hammadi Agrebi, Tunisia. DR Congo is anticipating to feel, for the second time, what it is like to compete in the biggest football tournament in the world. The Leopard of Congo will take on the Atlas Lions of Morocco. The first leg of the playoff will hold at Pentecost Martyrs, while the second leg will hold at Complexes Mohammed V at 8:30 pm. Egypt will host AFCON champions, Senegal, less than two months after the two nations battled it in the African Nations Cup finals. The first leg will kick off at Cairo International Stadium at 8:30 pm, while the Lions of Teranga will welcome the Pharaohs of Egypt at Me Abdoulaye Wade Stadium at 6.00 p.m. on March 29. The Indomitable Lions of Cameroun are hoping to extend their World Cup appearance to eight, as they battle Algeria at Stade de Japoma at 6.00 p.m. In return, Algeria will host Cameroun at Stade Mustapha Tchaker at 8:30 p.m., as they hope to extend their World Cup appearance to five.